teams.name: Greg Haft
teams.loan_because:
My name is Gregory Haft, and I'm in my Junior Year at the University of Arizona. I'm a member of Pi Kappa Phi and an the acting community service/philanthropy chair. In this role, I am responsible for all philanthropic and community service events sponsored by Pi Kappa Phi and manage the planning, promotion, and execution of such events.

I grew up in Plainview, New York, a town located in Long Island and attended Plainview-Old Bethpage/JFK High School. From a very early age, I was introduced to athletics and played basketball, baseball football, and other sports offering pee-wee leagues for young boys. This exposure has shaped my activities as an athlete since, and as I grew older, I began developing an interest in wrestling. I became a member of the high school wrestling team my freshman year at Plainview-Old Bethpage/JFK High School, and was a member of the varsity wrestling team through my graduation in 2011. While on my high school wrestling team, I had a pretty successful track record, taking second place in my weight division at county qualifiers as a sophomore, and placing 1st or 2nd at all regular season tournaments. I was named “All Conference” his Junior and Senior years of High School.

Upon graduating Plainview-Old Bethpage/JFK High School, I began my freshman year at University of Arizona as a part of the Class of 2015 as a part of the university’s undergraduate nursing program. My goal is to enter into a medical career centered around working closely with patients, providing nutritional education, but in a position that is heavily associated with nursing duties. My scholastic and extra-curricular activities on campus are mainly involved in the health and medical type clubs; HOSA – “Future Health Professionals” being the primary student organization I'm a part of. HOSA, or “Future Health Professionals”, is a student organization whose mission is to promote career opportunities in health care and to enhance the delivery of quality health care to all people. It is a national student organization endorsed by the U.S. Department of Education and the Health Science Education Division of ACTE. I have acted in an appointed chair position on the student management board for one year, and hope to continue being involved in shaping the organization's activities and adding to it's success.

In my spare time, I'm a huge fan of following TV Series' and am a huge music fan. I'm a big fan of Breaking Bad, The Walking Dead, Game of Thrones, and Homeland, as far as dramatic seasonal shows are concerned. I try to stay updated on news and updates about these shows, and really enjoy writing episode recaps. As far as music goes, I'm a big electronic and indie rock fan. Right now some of my favorite DJ's and bands are: Calvin Harris, Bastille, Disclosure, Boize Noize, The Black Keys, Neon Trees, and many many others.

teams.name: Becky's Hugs
teams.loan_because: Becky was unfailingly generous during her short life (2001-2010).  She loved freely and without limit, and never met anyone she considered to be a stranger.  She was always ready with a hug for anyone who needed one, even when they didn't know it yet.  Loaning Becky's memory keeps her love alive, spreading her love around the world!
teams.description:
We are a group of people who have been inspired by the love of a young lady named Becky, who was tragically killed 30 August 2010 at the age of 9½.  She loved unconditionally, and was always ready with a hug, even for complete strangers.  The living memorial of sharing hugs began immediately after her death, when her mother told her classmates to hug each other every day in her memory.  This team keeps Becky's love alive by sharing her hugs in the form of loans around the world.

To learn more about Becky and the impact of her short life, visit BeckysHugs.com, which will point you to the Becky's Hugs page on Facebook.  Look at the photos and videos to get a better idea about who Becky was, and check out the timeline to see the ways in which people have celebrated her memory and love.

Hugs to you!

teams.name: Candles for Dads
teams.loan_because: Dads are the best. We make loans to support hard-working dads, in memory of great dads passed.
teams.description:
When our dad passed from a sudden heart attack, we asked friends to light a candle in his memory. We received photos of candles from around the world, which provided comfort. This Kiva lending team is a virtual candle we're lighting in memory of great dads everywhere - their light and love will live on.

...................

HOW TO LOAN WITH OUR KIVA TEAM:

1. Join Kiva, then join our "Candles for Dads" Lending Team.
2. After you've joined our Lending Team, find a dad on Kiva to loan to and make a loan of $25 or more.
3. During checkout, select to have your loan count towards our "Candles for Dads" Kiva Team's collective impact. Thanks!

HOW TO FIND DADS ON KIVA TO LOAN TO:
1. Find a Featured Candles for Dads loan on our Team Activity page, or on our Facebook page: www.facebook.com/candlesfordads
2. Search for new dads to support on Kiva by clicking "Lend" in the Kiva main menu, then filter your search by gender and read profiles to find dads to loan to. Share your finds with us on facebook so we chip in as a group (we're still a small group, so plan to feature 1-2 loans a month for now). 
...................

HELP SHARE CANDLES FOR DADS:
1. Please connect with us on Facebook & Twitter and invite friends to join us:
Facebook: http://facebook.com/candlesfordads
Twitter: http://twitter.com/candlesfordads
Website: http://candlesfordads.org (forwards to Kiva Team Page)
2. Recruit friends to join our Kiva Lending Team. Kiva has some cool recruiting tools that (sometimes) even give you and friends who join a $25 credit to make loans when they join: http://www.kiva.org/team/CandlesForDads/recruit 
3. Volunteer Research for Dad Loan Suggestions: If you find a great dad on Kiva for us to loan to, share the Kiva profiles on our facebook page so others on our team can chip in to reach the goal. We will feature at least one C4D loan each month.
4. Share a memory of a great dad you are donating in memory of on our facebook and twitter.
......................

In memory of our dad, Shaman Mullick (1947 - 2012), and great dads everywhere. Your love and light live on.

teams.name: Guys holding fish
teams.loan_because: We feel an affinity for entrepreneurs that make their living by fishing, selling fish, or attempting to make their lives better because of their proximity to the ocean, or freshwater locales...
teams.description:
We love fish and/or fishing so much that many of us have chosen to present ourselves on KIVA with a photo of ourselves, holding a fish!  We welcome "gals" to join, as well, the name of the team notwithstanding...  

We certainly support "sustainable" fishing, but also recognize that sometimes, our "Western" views of resource management may not match the needs of the very desperate folks, in other countries, struggling to make a living, or even providing food for their families ...  Our intent is to help the struggling, without regard to their profession or trade.  We believe that our lending record well represents that goal, as we are a pretty diverse group, with very diverse lending interests....

teams.loan_because:
Everything you want to know about the Loan Taggers team is on this page. If you would like to make a suggestion, please send a private message to one of the team captains.

Loan Taggers was formed to coordinate the efforts of volunteers who will systematically review and tag all of the loans posted to the Kiva website. Having all loans reviewed and tagged to the same standards will enable lenders to find loans they are interested in faster, and can help to get loans funded before they expire.

Current tagging status: docs.google.com/spreadsheet
docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AkRBX8P18KLadHY0UllxZ3ljT2E2dlBYRXpEd3Blemc&usp=sharing
teams.description:
Tag Definitions: If you are just interested in the definitions we use for each tag, please go to 
http://kivaloantaggers.blogspot.com/2013/09/tag-definitions.html
Feel free to leave comments on how you would like a tag to be used or not used.

If you are interested in joining the Loan Taggers, please pick 
1) The weekday which you want to spend tagging your loans (say Saturday). 
2) 1-3 different sectors you want to tag (say Food). You can also sign up for Clean up Crew (loans closest to expiration, all sectors).
3) The number of loans you want to tag (30 or more. With a little practice you can tag 1 loan per minute, so 30 loans = 30 min).
4) Join the team and post your picks on the message board: "Saturday / Food / 30 loans"
5) Check the team board and your personal message folder the next Saturday for a list of 30 loans to be tagged.

teams.name: Candles for Dads
teams.loan_because: Dads are the best. We make loans to support hard-working dads, in memory of great dads passed.
teams.description:
When our dad passed from a sudden heart attack, we asked friends to light a candle in his memory. We received photos of candles from around the world, which provided comfort. This Kiva lending team is a virtual candle we're lighting in memory of great dads everywhere - their light and love will live on.

...................

HOW TO LOAN WITH OUR KIVA TEAM:

1. Join Kiva, then join our "Candles for Dads" Lending Team.
2. After you've joined our Lending Team, find a dad on Kiva to loan to and make a loan of $25 or more.
3. During checkout, select to have your loan count towards our "Candles for Dads" Kiva Team's collective impact. Thanks!

HOW TO FIND DADS ON KIVA TO LOAN TO:
1. Find a Featured Candles for Dads loan on our Team Activity page, or on our Facebook page: www.facebook.com/candlesfordads
2. Search for new dads to support on Kiva by clicking "Lend" in the Kiva main menu, then filter your search by gender and read profiles to find dads to loan to. Share your finds with us on facebook so we chip in as a group (we're still a small group, so plan to feature 1-2 loans a month for now). 
...................

HELP SHARE CANDLES FOR DADS:
1. Please connect with us on Facebook & Twitter and invite friends to join us:
Facebook: http://facebook.com/candlesfordads
Twitter: http://twitter.com/candlesfordads
Website: http://candlesfordads.org (forwards to Kiva Team Page)
2. Recruit friends to join our Kiva Lending Team. Kiva has some cool recruiting tools that (sometimes) even give you and friends who join a $25 credit to make loans when they join: http://www.kiva.org/team/CandlesForDads/recruit 
3. Volunteer Research for Dad Loan Suggestions: If you find a great dad on Kiva for us to loan to, share the Kiva profiles on our facebook page so others on our team can chip in to reach the goal. We will feature at least one C4D loan each month.
4. Share a memory of a great dad you are donating in memory of on our facebook and twitter.
......................

In memory of our dad, Shaman Mullick (1947 - 2012), and great dads everywhere. Your love and light live on.

teams.description:
The Armenia Team currently has 90 members supporting Armenian entrepreneurs. 

Whether they make cheese, herd sheep, sell shoes, or grow tomatoes, our team exists to support them in getting access to affordable loans all over Armenia.
 
Past and Present Kiva Fellows Serving in Armenia:

- Velizara Passajova KF8
- Brian Kelly KF9
- Suzanne Till KF9
- Alexis Ohanian KF10
- Liz Nagle KF10
- Peter Tashjian KF11
- Vanick Der Bedrossian KF12
- Abhishek Banerjee KF13
- Caree Edson KF14

As Kiva Fellows, we are here to support Kiva lending in Armenia. We will update team members with interesting news, and gladly answer any questions you may have.

Happy lending, and Go Team Armenia!

teams.name: Unitarian Universalists
teams.loan_because:
We believe in:
**The inherent worth and dignity of every person
**Justice, equity and compassion in human relations
**Acceptance of one another and encouragement to spiritual growth in our congregations
**A free and responsible search for truth and meaning
**The right of conscience and the use of the democratic process within our congregations and in society at large
**The goal of world community with peace, liberty, and justice for all
**Respect for the interdependent web of all existence of which we are a part.
teams.description:
We are UU congregations and individuals (including those who describe themselves as "active" or "backslid" or "interested friends" or "just looking") throughout the world.
